1) pwd - pwd stands for Print Working Directory. It is used to display the location or decription of the current directory in which user are working.

2) ls - ls is the list command in linux. This command is used to show the contents of your directory.

3) cd- cd stands for Change Directory. It is used to change the path or location of current working directory to another directory in which user want to work.

4) mkdir- mkdir stands for Make Directory. It is used to create directory.

5) rmdir- rmdir stands for Remove Directory. It is used to remove directory.
